Several years ago it became apparent that many of the fossil plants supposed to have been collected from the Lance formation of Wyoming, Montana, and the Dakotas were in reality obtained from beds which are above and younger than the Lance formation as originally defined.l It has seemed wise, there- fore, to limit the scope of this report to the description and discussion of plants known definitely to have come from the Lance formation at its type locality.
